  "response": "```dockerfile
# Stage 1: chef
FROM rust:1.78 AS chef
WORKDIR /app
RUN cargo install cargo-chef
COPY Cargo.toml Cargo.lock ./
COPY server/ server/
RUN cargo chef prepare --recipe-path recipe.json

# Stage 2: rust-builder
FROM chef AS rust-builder
WORKDIR /app
COPY --from=chef /app/recipe.json recipe.json
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends python3-dev
RUN cargo chef cook --release --recipe-path recipe.json
COPY Cargo.toml Cargo.lock ./
COPY server/ server/
RUN cargo build --release

# Stage 3: python-builder
FROM debian:bookworm-slim AS python-builder
WORKDIR /app
RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
    python3-venv \
    python3-pip \
    python3-dev \
    build-essential
RUN python3 -m venv /opt/venv
ENV PATH="/opt/venv/bin:$PATH"
RUN pip install --no-cache-dir torch --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cpu && \
    pip install --no-cache-dir transformers tokenizers safetensors

# Stage 4: runtime
FROM debian:bookworm-slim AS runtime

LABEL maintainer="ML Infrastructure Team" \
      version="1.0.0" \
      description="Rust + Python ML Inference Server"

RUN apt-get update && apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
    python3 \
    libpython3.11 \
    curl \
    && rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

RUN groupadd -g 1000 inference && \
    useradd -u 1000 -g inference -s /bin/bash -m inference

COPY --from=python-builder /opt/venv /opt/venv
ENV PATH="/opt/venv/bin:$PATH"
ENV VIRTUAL_ENV="/opt/venv"

# Assuming the binary output is named inference-server
# Using wildcard or direct path depending on Cargo.toml; fallback to find and copy if needed
RUN mkdir -p /usr/local/bin
COPY --from=rust-builder /app/target/release/inference-server /usr/local/bin/inference-server
RUN chmod +x /usr/local/bin/inference-server

USER inference
WORKDIR /home/inference

EXPOSE 8080

HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=5s --start-period=10s --retries=3 \
  CMD curl -f http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1

CMD ["/usr/local/bin/inference-server", "--port", "8080"]
